dct_description_sm: The line data layer represents road centerlines for Dane County, Wisconsin in 2000. The polygon data layer represents the area between road centerlines for Dane County, Wisconsin in 2000. They are a feature class within the geodatabase, DaneCounty_Roads_2000.gdb. The table represents type 5 streets for Dane County, Wisconsin in 2000. The datasets were originally published by the Wisconsin Department of Administration on March 21, 2001 using data from the United States Census Bureau.[This data layer is a line shapefile of the highways in the county, derived from the 2000 TIGER Line Files. It is referenced to the Wisconsin Transverse Mercator (WTM) projection system, North American Datum 1983 with the 1991 adjustment (NAD83/91).][This data layer is a line shapefile of the roads in the county, derived from the 2000 TIGER Line Files. It is referenced to the Wisconsin Transverse Mercator (WTM) projection system, North American Datum 1983 with the 1991 adjustment (NAD83/91).]
